 Var | Type | Default | Purpose |\n|---------|------|---------|---------|\n| `PORT` | number | 3100 | HTTP server port |\n| `DATABASE_URL` | string (required) | — | PostgreSQL connection string |\n| `DB_SCHEMA` | string | \"public\" | PostgreSQL schema name |\n| `RPC_URL` | string (required) | — | Solana RPC endpoint |\n| `WS_RPC_URL` | string | undefined | WebSocket RPC for subscriptions |\n| `SERVER_KEYPAIR` | string (JSON bytes) | required | Solana keypair for transactions |\n| `JWT_SECRET` | string | derives from keypair | JWT signing secret |\n| `SOLANA_CLUSTER` | string | \"devnet\" | Cluster name (devnet/mainnet) |\n| `CHALLENGE_TTL_SECONDS` | number | 300 | Auth challenge timeout |\n| `ACCESS_TOKEN_TTL_SECONDS` | number | 86400 | JWT access token lifetime |\n| `REFRESH_TOKEN_TTL_DAYS` | number | 14 | Refresh token lifetime |\n| `RATE_LIMIT_PER_WALLET` | number | 10 | Requests per wallet per window |\n| `RATE_LIMIT_GLOBAL` | number | 100 | Global requests per window |\n| `WORKER_POLL_INTERVAL_MS` | number | 1000 | Settlement worker poll frequency |\n| `ENTROPY_ACCOUNT` | string | \"SysvarS1otHashes…\" | SlotHashes sysvar address |\n| `MIN_SOL_BALANCE` | float | 0.1 | Health check balance threshold |\n\n**Key Details**:\n- `SERVER_KEYPAIR` is parsed as a JSON array of bytes from `solana-keygen` output\n- `JWT_SECRET` defaults to first 32 bytes of the keypair's secret key if not explicitly set\n- `DB_SCHEMA` is normalized and applied to the connection URL via search parameters\n\n---\n\n### **3. Environment Files**\n\n**`.env` (backend root)**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/backend/.env`\n\n```\nDATABASE_URL=postgresql://vscode@localhost:5432/rng_utopia_dev\nRPC_URL=https://lb.drpc.live/solana-devnet/AvfNVeH0_E7ajvkIaZ0OS6QiksDa5ZMR76q4qi5fk9AX\nSERVER_KEYPAIR=[147,107,233,7,66,229,25,102,...] # Full 64-byte keypair\nWS_RPC_URL=wss://lb.drpc.live/solana-devnet/AvfNVeH0_E7ajvkIaZ0OS6QiksDa5ZMR76q4qi5fk9AX\n```\n\n**`.env.devnet`**: Not found at monorepo root.\n\n**Schema loading**: Via `db-config.ts`:\n- Reads `DB_SCHEMA` env var\n- Defaults to `\"public\"` if not set\n- Applied to DATABASE_URL as `?options=-csearch_path={schema}`\n\n---\n\n### **4. Close Call Clock Worker (`closecall-clock.ts` - Full Content)**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/closecall-clock.ts`\n\n#### **Factory Signature**:\n```typescript\nexport function createCloseCallClockWorker(\n  deps: CloseCallClockDeps,\n): CloseCallClockWorker\n```\n\n#### **Dependencies Interface**:\n```typescript\nexport interface CloseCallClockDeps {\n  connection: Connection;\n  serverKeypair: Keypair;\n  pythPriceAccount: PublicKey;  // BTC/USD Pyth price account\n}\n```\n\n#### **Public Interface**:\n```typescript\nexport interface CloseCallClockWorker {\n  start(): void;\n  stop(): void;\n  readonly isRunning: boolean;\n  tick(): Promise<void>;  // Run a single tick manually\n}\n```\n\n#### **Key Behavior**:\n1. **On start**: Discovers existing open rounds (recovery after restart)\n2. **On each tick** (aligned to ~2s after minute boundaries):\n   - Settles the previous round (if exists and phase is OPEN)\n   - Creates a new round with Pyth open price\n3. **Settle logic**:\n   - Reads on-chain CloseCallRound + CloseCallConfig\n   - Reads Pyth price + exponent (raw byte offsets: price@73, expo@89)\n   - Pre-determines outcome (refund if 0 entries, 1 side, or same price)\n   - Builds and submits settle tx with retry logic (3 attempts, 2s delay)\n4. **Create logic**:\n   - Generates random 8-byte roundId\n   - Reads Pyth open price\n   - Builds and submits create_round tx\n4. **Timing**: Uses `setTimeout` with `msUntilNextMinute()` to align to minute boundaries\n\n#### **Constants**:\n- `PHASE_OPEN = 0` (on-chain phase value)\n- `TICK_OFFSET_MS = 2000` (delay after minute boundary)\n- `MAX_TX_RETRIES = 3`\n- `TX_RETRY_DELAY_MS = 2000`\n- Pyth price offset: 73 (discriminator 8 + write_authority 32 + verification_level 1 + feed_id 32)\n- Pyth expo offset: 89 (price offset + 8 bytes price + 8 bytes conf)\n\n#### **Error Handling**:\n- TX failures logged; retries 3 times before giving up\n- Settlement failures clear active round (timeout_refund on-chain will handle)\n- Account decode errors logged but worker continues\n- RPC errors logged but don't crash loop\n\n---\n\n### **5. Settlement Worker Pattern (`settlement.ts` - For Comparison)**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/settlement.ts`\n\nThe settlement worker shows the standard worker pattern:\n\n```typescript\nexport interface SettlementWorkerDeps {\n  db: Db;\n  connection: Connection;\n  serverKey: PublicKey;\n  pollIntervalMs: number;\n  onSettleReady?: (pda: string) => Promise<void>;\n  isFinalized?: (pda: string) => boolean;\n}\n\nexport function createSettlementWorker(deps: SettlementWorkerDeps): SettlementWorker {\n  return {\n    start(): void { /* init + loop */ },\n    stop(): void { /* cleanup */ },\n    get isRunning(): boolean { /* state */ },\n    poll(): Promise<void> { /* single cycle */ },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Pattern Details**:\n- Factory takes a deps object\n- Returns an object with `start()`, `stop()`, `isRunning`, and a `poll()` method\n- `start()` logs initialization state and schedules the loop\n- Loop wraps poll in try-catch, logs errors, and reschedules\n- Worker state is closure-captured (`running`, `timeoutId`)\n\n---\n\n### **6. How Workers Are Instantiated in `index.ts`**\n\n**Current workers started**:\n\n1. **Settlement Worker** (coinflip + lord):\n```typescript\nconst worker = createSettlementWorker({\n  db,\n  connection,\n  serverKey: config.serverKeypair.publicKey,\n  pollIntervalMs: config.workerPollIntervalMs,\n  onSettleReady: async (pda) => {\n    await retrySettler.attemptSettle(pda);\n    pdaWatcher.unwatch(pda);\n  },\n  isFinalized: (pda) => retrySettler.isFinalized(pda),\n});\nworker.start();\n```\n\n2. **PDA Watcher** (WebSocket-based instant join detection):\n```typescript\nconst pdaWatcher = createPdaWatcher({\n  connection,\n  serverKey: config.serverKeypair.publicKey,\n  onJoinDetected: async (pda, targetSlot) => {\n    // Update DB + settle if target slot passed\n  },\n});\n```\n\n3. **Retry Settler** (transaction retry + finalization tracking):\n```typescript\nconst retrySettler = createRetrySettler({\n  db,\n  connection,\n  settleRound: (pda) => settleRound({ db, connection, ... }, pda),\n});\n```\n\n**Notable**: `createCloseCallClockWorker` is **NOT** currently instantiated in `index.ts`. The close call routes are read-only (`createCloseCallRoutes({ db })`), and the clock worker would need to be added separately.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Logger & Database Initialization**\n\n**Logger** (`logger.ts`):\n- Exports a JSON-structured logger with `debug`, `info`, `warn`, `error` methods\n- Writes to stdout (info/debug/warn) or stderr (error)\n- Each entry includes timestamp, level, message, and optional context fields\n- No secrets logged (keypairs, private keys explicitly excluded)\n\n**Database** (`db.ts` + factories in `index.ts`):\n- `createDb(databaseUrl)` — returns Db with typed queries (rounds, operator events)\n- `createAuthDb(sql)` — returns AuthDb for JWT challenges/tokens\n- Both use `postgres` library with shared connection\n\n---\n\n### **Summary Table**\n\n| Component | File | Factory | Deps | Return Type |\n|-----------|------|---------|------|-------------|\n| Server Bootstrap | `index.ts` | N/A | config, db, connection | Hono app + Nodes server |\n| Config Loader | `config.ts` | `loadConfig()` | process.env | `Config` interface |\n| Settlement Worker | `settlement.ts` | `createSettlementWorker()` | `SettlementWorkerDeps` | `SettlementWorker` |\n| PDA Watcher | `pda-watcher.ts` | `createPdaWatcher()` | connection, serverKey, callback | `PdaWatcher` |\n| Retry Settler | `retry.ts` | `createRetrySettler()` | db, connection, settleRound fn | `RetrySettler` |\n| Close Call Clock | `closecall-clock.ts` | `createCloseCallClockWorker()` | `CloseCallClockDeps` | `CloseCallClockWorker` |\n| Logger | `logger.ts` | — | — | Logger singleton |\n| DB | `db.ts` | `createDb()`, `createAuthDb()` | databaseUrl or sql | `Db`, `AuthDb` |\n\n---\n\n### **Files Explored** (Absolute Paths)\n\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/index.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/config.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db-config.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/logger.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/closecall-clock.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/settlement.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/.env`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/package.json`\n\n---\n\n### **Key Takeaways for Close Call Worker Integration**\n\n1. **Factory Pattern**: `createCloseCallClockWorker(deps)` returns an object with `start()`, `stop()`, `isRunning`, and `tick()`\n2. **Dependencies**: Only needs `connection`, `serverKeypair`, and `pythPriceAccount` (PublicKey)\n3. **Config Injection**: The Pyth account address could come from an env var (similar to `ENTROPY_ACCOUNT`)\n4. **Startup Order**: Worker is created and started in `index.ts` before routes (like settlement worker)\n5. **No DB Needed**: Unlike settlement worker, clock worker is self-contained (no DB deps)\n6. **Timing**: Aligns to minute boundaries with 2s offset; logs all state changes with structured JSON"}],"totalDurationMs":92065,"totalTokens":52161,"totalToolUseCount":19,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":729,"cache_read_input_tokens":47935,"output_tokens":3494,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":729},"infer